 Syntax:  .set autoread    (it's a toggle)

Results:  Turns your autoreading feature on or off. This is a toggle 
	  command.
          Autoreading is, when you have new mail, it will say you
          have new mail AND proceed to read your mail.
          The toggle options are:
           1. off
              Doesn't read any new mail automatically.
           2. on logins only
              Only reads new mail when you login.
           3. online only
              Only reads new mail when you get it while you're online.
           4. on logins and online
              Reads new mail when you log in and when you get mail while
              you're online/on the talker.

          This setting is saved between logins.

See also: rmail, set_autofwd
